<subSubSection id="87B46525FFF2FFE8FF69557FFB1C2CD3" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF2FFE8FF69557FFECE2C76" blockId="13.[189,310,1843,1869]" box="[189,310,1843,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">
<heading id="945981C2FFF2FFE8FF69557FFECE2C76" bold="true" box="[189,310,1843,1869]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF2FFE8FF69557FFECE2C76" bold="true" box="[189,310,1843,1869]" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF2FFE8FF69552FFB1C2CD3" blockId="13.[187,1399,1890,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF2FFE8FE9D552FFE302C46" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,456,1891,1917]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="demaco" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF2FFE8FE9D552FFE302C46" box="[329,456,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">N. demaco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF2FFE8FE1B552FFDD32C46" box="[463,555,1891,1917]" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF2FFE8FCDA552FFC6E2C47" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[782,918,1891,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turquino">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF2FFE8FCDA552FFC6E2C47" box="[782,918,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">N. turquino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB3F4B5FFFF2FFE8FC73552FFB392C46" author="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G." box="[935,1217,1891,1917]" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" pagination="301 - 344" refId="ref12419" refString="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G. 2016. Neostasina gen. nov., a new genus of huntsman spiders from the Neotropical region (Araneae, Sparassidae, Sparianthinae). Zootaxa 4079: 301 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4079.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Rheims &amp; Alayón 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 143−145) by the epigyne with MS subrectangular. They are distinguished from the latter species by the ar mostly straight and posterior margin of MS at level with tips of posterior projections of LL (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF2FFE8FBA355E6FB372CFE" box="[1143,1231,1962,1989]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) (ar M-shaped and MS surpassing tips of posterior projections of LL in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF2FFE8FC825583FC252CD3" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[854,989,1999,2024]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turquino">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF2FFE8FC825583FC252CD3" box="[854,989,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="179">N. turquino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
