<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695344FEB62A19" blockId="15.[189,334,264,290]" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
<heading id="945981C2FFF0FFEAFF695344FEB62A19" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF695344FEB62A19" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF3E5374FE342A6A" blockId="15.[187,1400,311,519]" box="[234,460,311,338]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF3E5374FE342A6A" bold="true" box="[234,460,311,338]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
Female (
<typeStatus id="1015880CFFF0FFEAFE81537BFE3C2A6A" box="[341,452,311,337]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">holotype</typeStatus>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695310FB13293C" blockId="15.[187,1400,311,519]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
COLOR. Prosoma pale brown; cephalic region with faint lines extending posteriorly from PME; thoracic region with brown margins and scattered markings between thoracic striae; fovea brown; eye borders black. Chelicerae brownish orange, slightly darker than prosoma. Legs and palps pale brown with scattered brown spots. Labium and endites brown, distally pale brown. Sternum pale brown with slightly darker margins. Opisthosoma brownish gray; dorsally with few gray spots anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFB8E53A0FB58293C" box="[1114,1184,492,519]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[209,1368,676,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-49@14.[189,1399,664,1897]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607924/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A−B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695063FE75298E" blockId="15.[188,1399,558,694]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">MEASUREMENTS. Total length 10.3, prosoma length 5.1, width 3.4, opisthosoma length 4.6, width 3.0. Eye diameters: 0.23, 0.20, 0.15, 0.19; interdistances: 0.22, 0.17, 0.40, 0.36, 0.22, 0.10. Legs (2143): I: 12.3 (3.6, 2.0, 3.2, 2.8, 0.7); II: 12.8 (3.8, 2.0, 3.2, 3.0, 0.8); III: 10.0 (3.2, 1.6, 2.2, 2.3, 0.7); IV: 12.2 (3.9, 1.5, 2.5, 3.4, 0.9).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695092FBD929CC" blockId="15.[189,1057,733,760]" box="[189,1057,733,760]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
EPIGYNE. EF as long as wide; ar entire; MS wider than long (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFC545091FC2729CC" box="[896,991,733,759]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[209,1368,676,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-49@14.[189,1399,664,1897]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607924/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Figs 6C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFC385091FBEB29CC" box="[1004,1043,733,759]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">8A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF69516CFC892865" blockId="15.[188,1399,799,862]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
VULVA. GP longer than wide, postero-mediad; SP encapsulated within sclerotized structure, with internal ducts inconspicuous; FD postero-mediad (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFD7F510FFCF52866" box="[683,781,835,861]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[209,1368,676,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-49@14.[189,1399,664,1897]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607924" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607924/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Figs 6D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFCCD5108FCDE2865" box="[793,806,836,862]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">8</figureCitation>
B−C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="87B46525FFF0FFEAFF6951CAFA8E28F4" box="[189,1398,902,976]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" type="distribution">
